# No Re-Export Wrappers

When moving code between packages, do NOT create intermediate re-export files that just forward imports. Instead, update all consumers to import directly from the source package.

```typescript
// BAD — wrapper file that just re-exports
// packages/cli/src/lib/graphql/buildTranscendGraphQLClient.ts
export {
  buildTranscendGraphQLClient,
  buildTranscendGraphQLClientGeneric,
} from '@transcend-io/sdk';

// GOOD — consumers import directly from the source
import { buildTranscendGraphQLClient } from '@transcend-io/sdk';
```

When refactoring/moving functions between packages:

1. Move the implementation to the target package
2. Update ALL import sites to point to the new package directly
3. Delete the old file entirely — do not leave a re-export shim

This applies to both function re-exports and type re-exports. The only exception is a package's public barrel (`index.ts`), which is expected to re-export from submodules within the same package.
